<section id="itsm_taSource">
    <title>taSource</title>
    
    <para>Text Analysis Source - the <code>taSource</code> attribute is the <olink
            targetdoc="../xliff21.xml" targetptr="ITS20">[ITS]</olink> defined <code>taSource</code>
        attribute.</para>
    
    
    <para><emphasis>Value description:</emphasis> text string</para>
    <para>The text string is supposed to be a human or machine redable name of a collection of text
        analysis concept resources, in the sense of an <ulink
            url="http://www.w3.org/TR/its20/#textAnalysis-info-pieces"> identifier of the collection
            source</ulink>.</para>
    
    <para><emphasis>Default value:</emphasis>: undefined</para>
    
    
    
    <para><emphasis>Used in:</emphasis>
        <olink targetdoc="../../elements/inline/mrk.xml" targetptr="mrk"
            ><code>&lt;mrk></code></olink>, and
        <olink targetdoc="../../elements/inline/sm.xml"
            targetptr="sm"><code>&lt;sm></code></olink>.</para>
    
    <itemizedlist>
        <title>Constraints</title>
        <listitem><para>When the attribute <link linkend="itsm_taSource"><code>taSource</code></link> is set, the
                    <olink targetdoc="itsm_taIdent.xml" targetptr="itsm_taIdent"
                        ><code>taIdent</code></olink> attribute <glossterm>must</glossterm> be set
                as well.</para></listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    <para>See the <olink targetdoc="../../modules/itsm/Text_Analysis.xml" targetptr="taAnnotation">ITS Text Analysis Annotation</olink> for the full normative usage description of this attribute. Other advanced Constraints follow from that normative usage description.</para>
    
</section>
